# Feature + documentation

When adding or changing **user-facing behavior** (form sections, schema fields, PDF output, drafts, branding), update docs in the **same change** — not in a follow-up.

## Doc map (minimum)

| Code change | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| New/changed form or PDF section | `README.md`, `docs/IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| PDF layout or pricing rules | `docs/PDF-QA-CHECKLIST.md` |
| Focused feature (e.g. logo) | Relevant plan in `docs/` + mark status **Implemented** when done |

Skip doc updates only for pure refactors, dependency bumps, or internal tests with **no** behavior change.

## Commit

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) in **English**. Include doc files in the same commit as the feature.

```
feat(pdf): add car rental section to form and export

Document car rentals in README, architecture, implementation plan, and PDF QA checklist.
```

For the full workflow, use the **ship-feature** skill (`.cursor/skills/ship-feature/SKILL.md`).
